<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>The woman rushed to the Welkom cop shop to report the matter. Police spokesman Captain Stephen Thakeng said Sergeant Rabete Rabete and Constable Elias Khumalo were on duty when the matter was reported.“The woman arrived at about 1.30pm,” said Thakeng. “She told the cops that she left her vehicle and keys at a car wash garage in Othello Street.“She said she gave the car keys to a car wash assistant.“After a while, she went to back to fetch the car and found the premises closed and her vehicle missing.”Thakeng said a case of theft of a motor vehicle was registered. “Police worked tirelessly around the clock tracing the car. “The 29-year-old suspect was located and arrested,” said Thakeng.He advised motorists to be careful when taking their cars to a car wash. “It is advisable not to leave your car behind but rather wait until it is finished.” Welkom’s acting station commander, Colonel Didi Ramoolla praised the officers for acting swiftly.